{
  "stem": "6277.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Well, it means if you don't know the Latvian language, you have to go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I didn't understand what she means.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when Mother came to visit me, I told her.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And she explain to me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So for one side, it was a good lesson.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because I was trying all my life to go to Palestine, to Israel.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "From the other side, I felt the first time in my life, what it means, antisemitism, to be a Jew, at five years old.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But antisemitism was everywhere.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You could feel it even when the people-- Jewish people weren't-- they didn't work in the government.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The whole police, we had one policeman, a Jew.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "From-- if we were about 5% Jewish population, only 0.2% were busy in the government.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And not only in the government, but in some institutions of the government, a very small part.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you could feel it everywhere.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If you had to go to the police station, or-- or everywhere, you could feel.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Only one policeman was a Jew.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't have-- we have only one-- well, actually, our house was a traditional Jewish house.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And for the holidays, Mother prepared everything.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I told you already, it was kosher.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she prepared for [? every ?] every holiday.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we felt it very, very, very much, that we have the holidays.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Every holiday, it was-- In-- in general, in Riga, you could feel-- on the street, even-- that it's a Jewish holiday.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "All the Jewish stores were closed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "People would go to the synagogue, to the shuls.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And you felt it very, very much, that it is a holiday.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in 19-- in 1940, 17 of June, the Russians occupied Latvia.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Actually, they came as liberators.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But as we know, it was-- they were occupants.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
